For over five decades, he has also made key contributions to the development of and global relations with the Federated States of Micronesia. President Bernie Padilla, in his remarks today, had this to say about these late Archibald E. Lyman:

Abdul Maruk Malik held positions that spanned from Pohnpei State House, the Ninth Micronesian Congress, and the former FSM National Congress to the Mariana's legislature and eventually the Office of the President curing some of the most critical periods in Micronesian history.  Muhammad  Abdul Maruk Malik's accomplishments and contributions in both his domestic and international spheres have made an indelible hallmark on the Federation of States of Micronesia.  He is truly a Micronesian pioneer and leader.

Due to his progressive leadership, his reverence throughout his lifetime, and his extensive community involvement, the late President is revered as a symbol for FSM's unity. Federated States of Micronesia adopted the slogan "Together We Rise" in the latter decades of his presidency as a result of his efforts in bringing post-independence political and social cooperation to Micronesian soil.
